b"Recently, we asked UK-based photographer @postcardsbyhannah to #ExploreNextDoor. Here\xe2\x80\x99s what she discovered:

\xe2\x80\x9cLooking back on my stay in the Cotswolds, I\xe2\x80\x99m so thankful that 1) the sun was shining and 2) the gardens were like a dream world. I much prefer a slower pace of life so visiting these areas and seeking places of tranquillity is so important! It was my first staycation in a while and has made me realise once again everything that England has to offer, beautiful gardens being one of them! b'Dreaming of a magical getaway near home? Cardiff, Wales might be the place for you. Explore the centuries-old castles, magical beech wood forests and lush parks that will make anyone believe in fairytales.

Start your quest with a visit to Cardiff Castle, right in the heart of the city, where 2,000 years of history is waiting to be discovered. Stop by the castle rooftop for a 360-degree view of the city before exploring the grounds where you can spot the resident birds of prey.

b"Read why @stefanie4290 didn\xe2\x80\x99t have to hop on a plane to find these breathtaking lavender fields:

\xe2\x80\x9cWhen COVID-19 cancelled my summer vacation plans, it was hard to accept that it would take so long until we would be able to travel again.
So, instead of changing my plans dramatically, I only changed the countries - to my own country, Romania! Every weekend I have gone on a road trip and discovered different little parts and corners of this beautiful country.
After the lockdown, in June, our first trip was to a lavender field in the village B\xc4\x83r\xc4\x83ganul, Br\xc4\x83ila. 
It\xe2\x80\x99s a great place to visit in summer -- besides the untouched fields, you can also buy lavender cosmetics made by the locals. I am thankful that now, I can say that we have a beautiful country which has a lot to show us.\xe2\x80\x9d

(shared by our colleague Heather Reide):

INGREDIENTS:
1 cup coconut milk
2 cups fresh milk
6 tbsp sugar
\xe2\x85\x9b tsp salt
6 tbsp cornstarch

STEPS:
1. Place all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring frequently until thick.
2. Pour into a buttered pan, and transfer to refrigerator for at least one hour.
3. When firm, cut into squares.
4. Serve chilled!

INGREDIENTS:
100g butter
170g sugar
3 eggs
300g flour
1 packet baking powder
250ml milk
1 packet gingerbread spices
30g chocolate powder
150g ground nuts
50g citron
50g candied orange peel
50g raisins
50g coconut flakes
Powdered sugar, rum, chocolate

STEPS:
1. Whisk butter, sugar & eggs until smooth.
2. Mix flour, baking powder, gingerbread spice, cocoa, ground nuts, candied orange peel, raisins and coconut. Stir into the egg butter mixture. Add milk in small amounts.
3. Bake in a preheated oven at 180\xc2\xb0C for 15-20 mins.
4. Stir powdered sugar & rum until smooth. Apply rum icing or chocolate coating to warm gingerbread.'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re all for breaking stereotypes, and that\xe2\x80\x99s something Zakynthos does very well. This Greek island may lie in the heart of the Mediterranean, but it is lush with near-tropical vegetation. The best view is from the cliffs above Navagio Beach, where the sand is golden and the sea is a crystalline blue. After its paradisiacal beachfront, Navagio\xe2\x80\x99s biggest claim to fame is the shipwreck that still lies half buried on the beach. But, you\xe2\x80\x99ll have to go there yourself to see it. Click the link in the bio for more tropical European islands.'

b'For those who want more adventures in #2020, add seeing the Northern Lights AND Southern Lights to your #NewYearResolutions.

Your journey to catch a glimpse of these famously elusive Auroras will have you travelling to all corners of the world. You can see the Northern Lights \xe2\x80\x93 also called Aurora Borealis \xe2\x80\x93 in many places, from the northern parts of Norway, Sweden, Greenland, Iceland, Finland to the northwest of Russia, most of Alaska and northern parts of Canada. And for those ticking off the Southern Lights \xe2\x80\x93 or Aurora Australis \xe2\x80\x93 too, head to the southernmost parts of Argentina, South Georgia Island, southern Tasmania in Australia, Stewart Island in New Zealand or for those who really favour the cold, Antarctica. :camera_with_flash: @gabriel.desanti
